Friday August 30th 2013 3:55 am -04:00,you are defining functions in the shell. this is possible but it is much easier to separate the function definitions from the function calls. define functions in the editor and call the functions in the shell.howto1. open editor: file - new window2. define one or more functions in the editor: def square_print(num): etc...3. save your function(s) in a file: file - save as - any_name.py4. run the module (file) in the shell: run module5. call the function in the shell: square_print(4)this procedure is shown in the video defining functions around 4:48. , Resolved,0
